  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3712881044" />
    <a title="Donald Powell" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/15249098-donald-powell"><img alt="Donald Powell" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1533766872p2/15249098.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3712881044?book_show_action=true">Dec 29, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Donald Powell" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Donald Powell" href="/user/show/15249098-donald-powell">Donald Powell</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/15249098-donald-powell?shelf=other">other</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3712881044" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14492571399089162911">OMG what a great book. This is a simple philosophy, based upon the idea of Grace, of Christianity. It is all positive, kind, tolerant, patient, loving. The concept of LOVE is examined and explained in a way that opens a new vision of the truth of the Christian message or philosophy. The theory here is a wholesale avowed rejection of much of what the Christian Churches seem to say is Christianity. This work is well documented and supported by bible references, is consistent and logical. The book </span>
  <span id="freeText14492571399089162911" style="display:none">OMG what a great book. This is a simple philosophy, based upon the idea of Grace, of Christianity. It is all positive, kind, tolerant, patient, loving. The concept of LOVE is examined and explained in a way that opens a new vision of the truth of the Christian message or philosophy. The theory here is a wholesale avowed rejection of much of what the Christian Churches seem to say is Christianity. This work is well documented and supported by bible references, is consistent and logical. The book is an inspiring look at this popular religion in a fresh and meaningful way to explain a purpose in life. A very good little book, in simple language and thoughtful construction.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="14492571399089162911" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
