      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Annalise Nakoneczny" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Annalise Nakoneczny" href="/user/show/79689894-annalise-nakoneczny">Annalise Nakoneczny</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9781601428684" href="/book/show/25614375-the-ragamuffin-gospel">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/79689894-annalise-nakoneczny?shelf=2018">2018</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/79689894-annalise-nakoneczny?shelf=2021">2021</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/79689894-annalise-nakoneczny?shelf=2019">2019</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/79689894-annalise-nakoneczny?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2412987631" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8483892025663963847">Still a beautiful, encouraging portrait of grace. Manning helps his readers view themselves as they are- beloved ragamuffins- and God as he is- deeply loving, full of grace, and merciful beyond our understanding. This is a book that I&apos;ll need to read probably every year to remind myself of the truth it holds.<br/><br/>Another yearly read-through! I love this book so much. Manning is so compassionate with his readers and points them back to the love of God over and over again.</span>
  <span id="freeText8483892025663963847" style="display:none">Still a beautiful, encouraging portrait of grace. Manning helps his readers view themselves as they are- beloved ragamuffins- and God as he is- deeply loving, full of grace, and merciful beyond our understanding. This is a book that I'll need to read probably every year to remind myself of the truth it holds.<br /><br />Another yearly read-through! I love this book so much. Manning is so compassionate with his readers and points them back to the love of God over and over again.</span>
